<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17004] camel-servlet - Should not close HttpServletInputStream when reading body into stream caching</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17004</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-14823&quot; title=&quot;Support to disable the stream caching in camel-servlet from the camel context - once more&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-14823&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-14823&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When camel-jetty / camel-servlet reads into message body, then the servlet input stream is copied to a stream cache, and the original servlet input stream is closed when doing so.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However there may be other things on a app server that uses this input stream so we should not close it at this point.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
